channel.title: [help please]Need to get my server online
channel.description:
Hi. I can only get on my server on 127.0.0.1(default server). Do any of you know how to get on it by typing my server name in and logging in that way?
Or how do you log in by not using 127.0.0.1(default server)? If you can help it would be a big help. Thank you.
~lele~[br][size=1]Posted at: November 11, 2006, 07:18:31 PM[/size][hr]Help me please.

item.dc:creator: @mail1 mail`
item.description:
@mail1 wrote:

If you do download hamachi , google.com then search hamachi, then follow the little demo it gives you, make a network(s) name and pass’s. compile the server, give out the network usernames and pass’s and give the number at the top of the hamachi (IP). then people can go on it and you’r a hoster!

Or set up a no-ip adress, compile server give out the aderss and host it that way.
